  <hbml:notes>
    <hbml:note id="s" type="special">
      <hbml:p>Dismounted units<hbml:comment> (502, 503)</hbml:comment>: Treat as infantry</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>units, but with only 3 figures.</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p></hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>Crossing River: Normal rules apply. In </hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>addition roll one die each times a unit tries </hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>to cross.  Remove 1 Figure if die result is</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>same as unit.  Roll each turn unit remains</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>on hex.</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p></hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>Swamps<hbml:comment> (401, 501)</hbml:comment>: Block line-of-sight. They stop </hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>movement when entered.  Units on </hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>swamp have 1 die less when attacking.</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p></hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>Gini Lake<hbml:comment> (410, 510, 610)</hbml:comment>: Treat as rough terrain.</hbml:p>
      <hbml:p></hbml:p>
      <hbml:p>Remove 'Construct Fieldworks' from deck.</hbml:p>
    </hbml:note>
